By the time I typed the last sentence, the rain had stopped and a sliver of moonlight crept through the clouds. I leaned back, surprised by the energy buzzing in my veins. Sometimes, the hardest step is simply beginning, even if you start with a sigh and a promise to yourself. Exhaustion, I realized, was not always a barrier—it was sometimes the threshold to something new.

